title: Past Projects
text: Caleb: When I was 17, I wrote and recorded my first album of mostly folk songs, titled Rainstorm Heart

title: Maeve
text:
This website will be about me learning and perfecting crochet! Here is some information about me:

I am currently a grad student at Cornell, but before this I did fieldwork in wildlife conservation
I started crocheting in December 2025, with a Maeve the Duck Woobles kit
After the woobles kit, I worked on some smaller projects, like a cowboy hat for my cat and some leaf bookmarks

title: Future Projects
text:
In the future, I would like to make headphone covers for my headphones because the leather is crumbling off the foam on them.
Caleb: A future project I’d like to try is writing songs with bird sounds interspersed in the music.

title: Current Projects
text:
I am currently working on a cardigan, the pattern is called “Euphoria Cardi”. My grandmother gave me the pattern and the yarn for it because she started it but never finished.
Caleb: I’m sadly not much of a crochet artist yet, but I can jot down some of my musical creations. I’m currently working on a song, in a Western theme, titled Prairie Moon, based on the Great Basin ecosystems of Oregon and Nevada.
